post_text: We are so excited to see everyone on Thursday. We will start the year by using the south doors. Bus drop off will be on the south side. Please enter the parking lot from the east and exit to the west. Students will need to be masked on the bus. Students will also need to be masked when on their feet (passing time, moving from one area to another, waiting in lunch line, etc). Students seated and socially distanced will be allowed to remove their mask. Students may bring their own mask and will be issued 2 masks.

HELP WANTED
Full Time Position

Elwood Public School is accepting applications for a custodian. Wage will be $12.80 per hour. This position includes single insurance bc/bs benefits. This position is an evening position or can be adjusted to an overnight position. During the summer, the position will be adjusted to a daytime shift. If interested, please fill out an application at the office of the Superintendent, Elwood Public School, 502 First Avenue, Elwood, Nebraska 68937. Phone: (308) 785-2491. Position open until filled.

Elwood Schools is an Equal Opportunity Employer. This position is subject to Veteran’s preference.

post_text:
It's almost August but an August unlike any other. School will open for students on August 13th with a new addition we're excited about and plans in place to keep everyone as safe as possible in light of the ongoing coronavirus concerns. Plans have been put in place and there are three documents linked below you will want to read. The first, entitled Elwood Re-opening Plan is a broad overview on all areas of our return to classroom learning. The second, listed as Elwood School Fall Re-opening Guidelines is a chart listing the restrictions and protocol the school will follow depending on the Two Rivers Public Health Department Risk Dial for our area. The final document, Hi-Line Extracurricular Covid Policy outlines the steps we are taking along with Eustis/Farnam in regards to our athletes.

Elwood Re-Opening Plan https://5il.co/isqk
Elwood School Fall Re-opening Guidelines https://5il.co/isql
Hi-Line Extracurricular Covid Policy https://5il.co/isqm

We look forward to seeing everyone on the 13th. Stay safe.

post_text: I have been asked several times in the past few days about the lunch program. Do we intend to continue serving meals for lunch.?Yes absolutely. Will there be a break in service? No there will not be a break. We intend to continue meals right into our normal summer service. What do you need to do? If you are in the list, stay on the list. If you wish to be added to the list give us a call. Otherwise everything will continue as it has since March. The Board of Education was very supportive of this program at our May meeting on Monday and we have no intention of interrupting our service of lunch.

What are your plans after high school?
I plan on attending Mid-Plains Community College.

See the Grand Canyon
Go to Yellowstone National Park

My favorite memory from high school was the district final game before we made it to state for volleyball and being at the state tournament as a player. Also all the fun memories with my friends.

SENIOR SPOTLIGHT
JUAN FLORES

What are your plans after high school, (college you plan to attend, etc.)

Attend the University of Notre Dame and major in Biological Sciences with a pre-medicine route in order to attend medical school after I graduate from college.

When I was young I used to imagine myself as a doctor or dentist.

What is your favorite high school memory?
Some of my favorite memories in high school are from the time I spent with my classmates during lunch because we would have some very interesting conversations. I think that these moments will probably be one of the things I will miss the most from high school.

SENIOR SPOTLIGHT
GRACIE CAMPBELL

What are your plans after college?
I plan to go to Central Community College and earn an Associates Degree in Criminal Justice. I would like to pursue my dreams and become a Police Officer.

What are three things you must do in your lifetime?
1. Swim with sharks
2. Go to Paris
3. Become a Cop

What is your favorite high school memory?
I have too many favorite memories. If I had to pick one, it would be moving up here from Norton, Kansas. I’ve made a few good friends and learned how to turn my attitude about school around. I don’t think I’m ready to graduate yet, but I
guess, it’s time to get out into the world.

post_text: Yesterday, 3rd grade students designed a house that wouldn’t blow away in the “wind” for science. Today, we had our contractor, Clint, come in and explain how foundations/footings, anchor bolts, studs, roofs, etc. all go into building a structure that doesn’t blow away in the wind! Everything is connect so that foundation keeps us in place! We’re loving all the real life learning with this construction on site! Next week we can hopefully see the actual footings for this new construction!
